body:
Basically it means choosing r things out of n, where order doesn't matter, and you are allowed to pick a thing more than once. For example, $\{1, 1, 2\}$ out of $\{1, 2, 3, 4\}$. I managed to find another solution: $$
{n \choose r} + (r-1){n \choose r-1} + (r-2){n \choose r-2} + \cdots + {n \choose 1}
$$ I am having trouble proving that these two are equivalent.
